wikipedia_page.main: Adrian Waller (born 26 December 1989 in Enfield) is a professional squash player who represents England. He reached a career-high world ranking of World No. 17 in November 2019.

response: Zac won a gold medal at the 2018 Commonwealth Games on the Gold Coast teamed with David Palmer defeating Daryl Selby and Adrian Waller of England (11–9, 3-11, 11-6).David Palmer (squash player) In doubles Zac also won a Silver Medal at the World Doubles in Darwin in 2016 and a Gold Medal at the Malaysian Open Doubles Championships later the same year. This has been a very successful period for Zac who made the Australian doubles team for the 2014 Commonwealth Games in Glasgow but was forced to leave the games early.
